HEADWORD: Schizophyte
<hw>Schiz"o*phyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Schizo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a plant.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>One of a class of vegetable organisms, in the classification of
Cohn, which includes all of the inferior forms that multiply by fission,
whether they contain chlorophyll or not.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

